# Repo workflow

This repository ships Home Assistant’s core **Verisure** integration as a **custom component** under `custom_components/verisure/`. The tree is refreshed from [home-assistant/core](https://github.com/home-assistant/core), not authored standalone.

## Pipeline

1. **Tracked patches** live in `patches/` (diff paths use `custom_components/verisure/`).
2. `./scripts/update.sh` rewrites paths into **`regenerated_patches/`** (gitignored), applies those patches onto a shallow clone of [home-assistant/core](https://github.com/home-assistant/core), copies `homeassistant/components/verisure` → `custom_components/verisure/`, and updates `hacs.json` and `manifest.json`. Run `./scripts/regenerate_patch.sh` alone only if you want the regenerated files without a full sync.

CI (`.github/workflows/sync-code.yml`) runs `./scripts/update.sh` and commits **`custom_components/verisure` only**. Commit **`patches/`** changes in PRs when you intend to change durable behavior (`regenerated_patches/` is not versioned).

## Editing guidance

- **Lasting divergences from upstream**: implement via **`patches/`** (then run `./scripts/update.sh` locally to verify), not only by editing `custom_components/` (the next sync can overwrite unpatched files).
- **Ephemeral edits** under `custom_components/` without a matching patch are fragile.

## Scope of this fork

`main` should match **core `master` + merged [#171317](https://github.com/home-assistant/core/pull/171317) + merged vsure 2.7.1**, implemented via patches until those land upstream.

**Intentional ongoing divergences:**

- `02-custom-scan-interval.patch` — shorter poll interval
- `04-pin-vsure.patch` — vsure from `python-verisure` branch `fix-mfa-single-login-and-stepup-rate-limit` until PyPI release

Regenerate `01-session-resilience-and-cleanup.patch` when the HA PR branch changes. Do not document this fork’s patch plan in homeassistant-core or python-verisure.
